# Form Handling — React Hook Form + Zod

## Approach

- **Simple inputs**: `useState` for controlled fields
- **Complex forms**: React Hook Form + Zod; always name the form instance `form`

## Schema Pattern

```typescript
import { z } from 'zod';

export const createDocumentSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1, 'Title is required'),
  content: z.string().min(1, 'Content is required'),
});

export type CreateDocumentFormData = z.infer<typeof createDocumentSchema>;
```

## Form Setup

```typescript
import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';

const form = useForm<CreateDocumentFormData>({
  resolver: zodResolver(createDocumentSchema),
  defaultValues: { title: '', content: '' },
});
```

## Validation

- Validate with Zod `safeParse` before submission when not using `zodResolver`
- Collect field errors by path for display
- Mutations triggered in handler hooks after validation passes

## Rules

- Check existing Zod schemas before creating new ones
- Form submission handlers live in `use{Page}Handlers` hooks
- Use shadcn `Form`, `FormField`, `FormItem`, `FormLabel`, `FormMessage` components
- Never bypass validation with type assertions on form data

See [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) Form Handling section.
